s with authorization2star  aIm Fokus des Bandes stehen die Arbeiten jüdischer Exeget*innen und Übersetzer*innen des 19. und 20. Jahrhunderts. Diese werden im Kontext der entstehenden historisch-kritischen Bibelwissenschaft beleuchtet und in ihrem Einfluss auf jüdische Bildungsbereiche reflektiert. Dabei werden Fragen nach ideengeschichtlichen Perspektiven sowie gezielt jüdischen Interessenschwerpunkten in Ergänzung zur überwiegend protestantischen Bibelwissenschaft gestellt.  aThe volume focuses on the work of 19th and 20th century Jewish interpreters and translators of the Bible. It examines their work in the context of the emergence of historical-critical biblical scholarship and evaluates their influence on aspects of Jewish education. The study raises questions about philosophical perspectives and specific areas of concern for Jewish scholars that went beyond those of predominantly Protestant biblical scholarship.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aChristianity and other religionsxJudaism. 0aHaskalahzGermanyxHistory. 0aJews, German. 0aJudaismzGermanyxHistory. 4aBibelinterpretation. 4aHaskala. 4aWissenschaft des Judentums. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aBiblical interpretation.1 aAurin, Hans-Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBezzel, Hannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGafni, Chanan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGottlieb, Michah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHecht, Louise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerrmann, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrone, Kerstin von der, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb